quran[27]{c,v,t}:
  17,23,"And your Master ordered that do not serve except Him, and be good to your parents. If one of them or both of them reaches old age with you, do not say ugh (or yuck) to them and do not snap at them (or drive them away), and talk to them honorably (and kindly)"
  17,24,"And spread the wing of humility (and respect) for them out of kindness, and say: my Master, have mercy on them as they nurtured me from childhood"
  17,25,"Your Master knows best what is in your minds. If you are righteous, then indeed He is forgiving for all who are repentant (and turn to Him)"
  17,26,"And give the relative (and close one) his due, as well as the needy and the traveler (in need), and do not spend wastefully (and excessively)"
  17,27,"Indeed those who spend wastefully (and excessively) are brothers of the devils, and the devil is ungrateful to his Master"
  17,28,"And if you turn away from them looking for a mercy from your Master that you hope for it, then speak to them in soft (and courteous) words"
  17,29,And do not make your hand chained to your neck (being tightfisted) and do not stretch it out to its utmost extent (being excessive) so you sit down blameworthy and regretful
  17,30,Indeed your Master increases the provision for anyone He wants and decreases it (for whom He wants). Indeed He is well informed and watchful of his servants
  17,31,"And do not kill your children for fear of poverty, as We provide for them and for you. Killing them is indeed a great sin"
  17,32,"And do not go near adultery (and fornication), indeed it is indecent and a bad way"
  17,33,"And do not kill anyone as God made it sacred (or forbidden), except in just cause. And anyone who is killed wrongfully, then We have given his heir authority (to forgive or take ransom or retaliate). So do not be excessive in the killing, indeed he is helped"
  17,34,"And do not go near orphan’s property until he reaches maturity except in the best way. And fulfill the promise, as the promise is a responsibility (and will be questioned about)"
  17,35,"And give full measure when you measure, and weigh with accurate scale. That is good and better in the end"
  17,36,"And do not follow what you don’t have knowledge of it. Indeed the ear and the eye and the heart, each of them is responsible for that"
  17,37,"And do not walk on the earth overjoyed (and selfishly), as you will never crack the earth and you will never reach the mountains in height"
  17,38,Badness of all that is disliked by your Master
  17,39,"That is from what your Master revealed to you of the wisdom. And do not set up another god with God, otherwise you will be thrown into hell blameworthy and banished"
  17,40,"Did your Master choose sons for you, and He took daughters from the angels? Indeed you say an outrageous word"
  17,41,"And We have certainly explained (the truth) in various ways in this Quran so that they take notice, but it only increases their disgust (and hatred)"
  17,42,"Say: if as they say there were gods with Him, then they would have certainly looked for a way toward the owner of the throne"
  17,43,Glory to Him (He is flawless) and He is greatly superior and above what they say
  17,44,"The seven skies and the earth and everyone in them glorify Him. And there is nothing that does not glorify Him with His praise, but you do not understand their glorifying. Indeed He is patient and forgiving"
  17,45,"And when you read the Quran, We place an invisible barrier between you and those who do not believe in the hereafter"
  17,46,"And We put coverings on their hearts and a deafness in their ears that they do not understand it (the Quran),. And when you mention your Master’s oneness in the Quran, they turn their backs in disgust (and hatred)"
  17,47,"We know better what they listen to it when they listen to you and when they talk secretly (and privately), when the wrongdoers say: you only follow a bewitched man"
  17,48,"See how they give examples of you, therefore they lost (the right path) and they cannot find a way"
  17,49,"And they said: are we raised in a new creation when we are bones and decomposed fragments"